Cell.Text: Miraak served me well, and was rewarded. I can grant you the same power as he wields, but all knowledge has its price.
Well done, my champion. Your journey towards enlightenment has finally led you here, to my realm, as I knew it would.
All seekers of knowledge come to me, sooner or later.
I am Hermaeus Mora, the Gardener of Men, knower of the unknown, master of fates. You stand in my realm, mortal.
<<Shared>> You have entered my realm. You have sought out the forbidden knowledge that only one other has obtained. | You are Dragonborn, like Miraak before you. A seeker of knowledge and power.
What do you want of me this time?
<<Shared>> You have entered my realm. You have sought out the forbidden knowledge that only one other has obtained. | You are Dragonborn, like Miraak before you. A seeker of knowledge and power.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMIntroA2: What do you want of me?

Cell.Text: No. Not yet. I have watched your progress through my realm with growing interest. | You are following in the footsteps of my servant Miraak. Like him, you are Dragonborn, and seek the power that is your birthright.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMIntroA3: Don't worry, I was just leaving.

Cell.Text: Your progess since obtaining my Oghma Infinium has been rapid. And now, I find you here, following in my servant Miraak's footsteps. | You also are Dragonborn. You also seek to learn how to bend the world to your will.
<<Shared>> You have entered my realm. You have sought out the forbidden knowledge that only one other has obtained. | You are Dragonborn, like Miraak before you. A seeker of knowledge and power.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMIntroA4: What do you want of me, my lord?

Cell.Text: [S] G|All that he knows he learned from me.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMSeekWordA1: Yes, I came here to learn Miraak's secrets.

Cell.Text: [S] G|You will serve me, willing or not. All who seek after the secrets of the world are my servants.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMSeekWordA2: I won't serve you, demon. I just want to defeat Miraak.

Cell.Text: [S] G|No. Look around you. You have done nothing here on your own. | You could spend a hundred lifetimes searching my library, and you will never find what you seek.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMSeekWordA3: I don't need your help. I'll learn Miraak's secrets on my own.

Cell.Text: You please me, champion. Your loyalty will be richly rewarded.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMSeekWordA4: Tell me what you want, my lord, and I will bring it to you.

Cell.Text: Knowledge for knowledge.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMSeekWordB1: So what's your price for the final Word of Power?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> The Skaal have withheld their secrets from me for many long years. The time has come for this knowledge to be added to my library.
[S] G|I know you will. And then I will give you the knowledge that you seek.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMFinalResponses1: I will talk to the Skaal and bring you their secrets.

Cell.Text: [S] G|My servant Miraak would have found a way to bring me what I want. So will you, if you wish to surpass him.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMFinalResponses2: What if the Skaal refuse to give up their secrets?

Cell.Text: [S] G|Yes, I know. And then Miraak's power will be yours as well.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMFinalResponses3: I will do as you command, my lord.

Cell.Text: Even dragons submit to Miraak's Voice. Without that power, you cannot face him. So say I, Hermaeus Mora, master of the tides of Fate.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMSeekWordB2: Why do I need this Word of Power to defeat Miraak?

Cell.Text: [S] G|My word is as true as fate, as inevitable as destiny. Bring me what I want, and I will give you what you seek.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMFinalResponses4: How do I know I can trust you, demon?

Cell.Text: He has served me long and well. But he grows restless under my guidance. | His desire to return to your world will spread my influence more widely. But it will also set him free from my direct control. | It may be time to replace him with a more loyal servant. One who still appreciates the gifts that I have to offer.

Node.Caption: DLC2MQ05HMSeekWordB3: Isn't Miraak your ally? Why help me defeat him?
